x4freetext: TWAC-ITEP multipurpose accelerator
complex
The selection of fragments was performed on the
basis of correlation distributions of the time of
flight from the time-to-digital converter and the
amplitude of the signal from the charge-to-digital
converter at various rigidity tunings of the
magneto-optical channel.
The FRAGM facility was used to detect ions.
Scintillation counters of FRAGM facility were
used to perform amplitude and time-of-flight
measurements.
The target was a beryllium foil 50 mu-m thick.
To obtain the absolute values of the differential cross
sections, a normalization to the total cross section
for the interaction of carbon ions with a beryllium
target was used.
Statistical error
Entry was approved by Dr. A.A.Kulikovskaya.
